<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-26T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-26T03:00:00-05:00" n="279" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">694.113Lumber/121: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Neville</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-26T17:00:00+09:00">November 26, 1929—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 26—9:40 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>110. Department’s instruction 587 [<hi rend="italic">588</hi>], August
                            1st, I have had conference with the Vice Minister for Foreign Affairs.
                            He informs me that the committee has not yet reached a discussion of the
                            lumber tariff and asked me for a formal note setting forth the American
                            position. I shall prepare and send such note using Department’s
                            instruction as a basis and refer to my conversation with Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs of August 30th.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Neville</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>